1
00:00:00,600 --> 00:00:01,667
<i> We're all here together.</i>

2
00:00:01,667 --> 00:00:03,167
[BREATHING SHAKILY]
<i> We're going to be okay.</i>

3
00:00:03,167 --> 00:00:05,300
<i> I promise you that, sister.</i>

4
00:00:05,300 --> 00:00:08,100
<i>You all think that my dad is
doing something wrong.</i>

5
00:00:08,100 --> 00:00:10,333
<i>Jade, it's not right that
we keep meeting in secret.</i>

6
00:00:10,333 --> 00:00:11,533
<i> This will hurt both of us.</i>

7
00:00:12,233 --> 00:00:14,033
<i> I'd like to file a report.</i>

8
00:00:14,033 --> 00:00:16,267
<i>Marina is working for Dad,
Sir Henri.</i>

9
00:00:16,267 --> 00:00:18,600
<i>So I won't be surprised
if she had a hand</i>

10
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:20,600
<i> in setting up Leon Almazan.</i>

11
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:22,300
<i> You're under arrest</i>

12
00:00:22,300 --> 00:00:26,133
<i>for conspiracy, bribery,
and obstruction of justice.</i>

13
00:00:26,133 --> 00:00:28,033
<i>Why are you arresting me?
I didn't do anything!</i>

14
00:00:28,033 --> 00:00:29,600
<i>You have the right
to hire a lawyer.</i>

15
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:31,367
<i>What's happening?
Why is he being released?</i>

16
00:00:31,367 --> 00:00:32,700
<i> He posted bail.</i>

17
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:34,133
<i> You are a murderer.</i>

18
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:37,067
<i> I didn't kill anyone.</i>

19
00:00:37,667 --> 00:00:39,200
<i>You may get away
with what you've done today,</i>

20
00:00:39,200 --> 00:00:40,633
<i>but we won't stop
coming after you...</i>

21
00:00:41,400 --> 00:00:42,667
<i> Andy Arellano.</i>

22
00:00:45,100 --> 00:00:47,633
[TRIXIE] Sari,
isn't Gio home yet?

23
00:00:47,633 --> 00:00:49,200
[SARI] I haven't seen him since.

24
00:00:49,567 --> 00:00:50,700
[EXHALES] What?

25
00:00:51,167 --> 00:00:52,533
They've been at the station
for so long.

26
00:00:52,533 --> 00:00:53,600
What's going on?

27
00:00:54,233 --> 00:00:56,133
I hope that Andy never gets out.

28
00:00:56,133 --> 00:00:58,133
Andy is powerful and rich.

29
00:00:58,567 --> 00:01:00,433
You know how things are
these days.

30
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:02,733
Money can do a lot.

31
00:01:02,733 --> 00:01:06,233
Hey, Trixie and her family
are rich too, right?

32
00:01:07,367 --> 00:01:11,300
Yeah, but we don't use money
and connections to be greedy.

33
00:01:11,300 --> 00:01:13,100
That Andy guy is on
a whole different level.

34
00:01:13,500 --> 00:01:15,167
He's a monster.

35
00:01:15,600 --> 00:01:18,233
Cheska, haven't you known a
lot about this for a while now?

36
00:01:19,633 --> 00:01:22,633
You and Trixie witnessed
Juan's kidnapping.

37
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:24,400
And...

38
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:28,100
And your camera recorded Marina
handing money to the goons.

39
00:01:29,133 --> 00:01:30,400
Wait, Raphie, where are you
going with this?

40
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:31,367
What's your point?

41
00:01:31,367 --> 00:01:32,633
[RAPHIE] What I mean is...

42
00:01:32,833 --> 00:01:35,167
your investigation is actually
getting somewhere.

43
00:01:37,533 --> 00:01:40,700
And now, I won't stop you.
I'm joining you.

44
00:01:43,133 --> 00:01:45,633
I just want justice
for Monette's death.

45
00:01:45,633 --> 00:01:52,567
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

46
00:01:55,200 --> 00:02:02,200
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

47
00:02:55,267 --> 00:02:57,333
What? And just like that,
he's free again?!

48
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:59,567
There's nothing I can do.

49
00:02:59,567 --> 00:03:01,167
Posting bail is legal.

50
00:03:02,900 --> 00:03:04,200
[KIKO] Because of that,

51
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:06,500
we're in even more
danger now.

52
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:12,600
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

53
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:14,733
Oh, wait. What's with that look?

54
00:03:15,833 --> 00:03:16,900
You should leave.

55
00:03:18,433 --> 00:03:19,633
- [CHESKA] What?
- Both of you.

56
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:21,600
What?

57
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:23,433
Martin, no!

58
00:03:23,433 --> 00:03:24,433
Kiko...

59
00:03:24,433 --> 00:03:26,233
No! What about you?
What about all of you?

60
00:03:26,233 --> 00:03:29,367
Martin, you know for a fact
that Cheska and I helped.

61
00:03:29,367 --> 00:03:30,467
We've done it before.

62
00:03:30,467 --> 00:03:31,900
- We can do it again!
- [MARTIN] Trixie, enough.

63
00:03:32,767 --> 00:03:34,500
You've done enough.

64
00:03:34,933 --> 00:03:36,400
We're grateful for that,

65
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:38,267
but we can't risk
your lives here.

66
00:03:38,733 --> 00:03:39,800
Okay?

67
00:03:40,767 --> 00:03:43,633
Martin, I'm not leaving you.

68
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:45,700
[GIO] Listen to your brothers.

69
00:03:46,733 --> 00:03:48,400
They're just thinking
about your safety.

70
00:03:49,533 --> 00:03:50,667
So, Cheska...

71
00:03:51,233 --> 00:03:53,467
Go back home.
Mama needs you more there.

72
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:54,633
Bro, come on!

73
00:03:54,667 --> 00:03:56,833
Stop being so hardheaded,
Cheska.

74
00:03:57,967 --> 00:03:59,567
[GIO] I already called
the boatman.

75
00:03:59,900 --> 00:04:01,400
He should be here anytime.

76
00:04:02,967 --> 00:04:04,333
Start packing.

77
00:04:05,233 --> 00:04:06,300
[CHESKA] Kiko...

78
00:04:06,300 --> 00:04:09,600
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

79
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:13,467
[BOAT ENGINE ROARING]

80
00:04:18,733 --> 00:04:19,767
Cheska!

81
00:04:19,767 --> 00:04:20,733
Cheska, wait.

82
00:04:20,733 --> 00:04:21,700
Hold on.

83
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:23,733
What is it now, Trixie?

84
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:25,300
Let's not go.

85
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:28,000
Come on, Trixie.

86
00:04:28,033 --> 00:04:29,600
Kiko is going to get mad at me.

87
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:31,000
And your brother
will be mad at you too.

88
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,300
Cheska, wait.

89
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:33,967
Come on, please.

90
00:04:33,967 --> 00:04:35,500
Are you going to back out now?

91
00:04:35,833 --> 00:04:38,333
Girl, you're one of the bravest
people I know.

92
00:04:38,333 --> 00:04:39,600
Why give up now?

93
00:04:40,733 --> 00:04:42,000
Do it for Monette.

94
00:04:42,667 --> 00:04:43,933
For our brothers.

95
00:04:44,933 --> 00:04:46,600
Cheska, please, come on.

96
00:04:46,967 --> 00:04:49,733
I can't do this without you.
You know that.

97
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,833
Girls, the boat's already here.

98
00:04:53,433 --> 00:04:54,700
They're just waiting for you.

99
00:04:57,267 --> 00:04:58,333
We're getting on.

100
00:04:59,733 --> 00:05:00,700
What?

101
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:02,900
I thought...

102
00:05:05,767 --> 00:05:08,467
Raphie, we're getting
on that boat, but...

103
00:05:08,467 --> 00:05:10,300
we're not going to Manila.

104
00:05:10,900 --> 00:05:12,500
We're going to help you.

105
00:05:15,033 --> 00:05:16,933
But wait, where will we live?

106
00:05:16,933 --> 00:05:18,533
We can't stay here
at the hotel,

107
00:05:18,533 --> 00:05:21,567
and our brothers can't
find out we didn't go home.

108
00:05:24,367 --> 00:05:26,733
I think I have an idea.

109
00:05:28,933 --> 00:05:30,433
[AUTOMATED VOICE]
<i> The number you have dialed</i>

110
00:05:30,433 --> 00:05:31,433
<i> cannot be reached.</i>

111
00:05:31,433 --> 00:05:32,933
<i> Please try again later.</i>

112
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,067
Edward!

113
00:05:36,067 --> 00:05:38,000
[SIGHS SHARPLY]

114
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:42,900
- [PHONE BEEPS]
- Is that Edward?

115
00:05:47,967 --> 00:05:49,467
You can't reach him?

116
00:05:50,533 --> 00:05:51,633
Yes.

117
00:05:52,333 --> 00:05:53,533
He blocked me
on everything.

118
00:05:53,533 --> 00:05:55,667
I just want to talk to him.

119
00:05:55,667 --> 00:05:57,400
Let's go see him.

120
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:59,633
- Huh?
- Let's go see him.

121
00:05:59,633 --> 00:06:00,667
Kiko?

122
00:06:01,633 --> 00:06:03,833
Let's go.
Before I change my mind.

123
00:06:05,033 --> 00:06:07,667
- But, Kiko--
- Come on, Jade.

124
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:08,867
Let's visit him.

125
00:06:08,867 --> 00:06:10,067
Wait, my bag.

126
00:06:16,933 --> 00:06:18,067
What's on your mind?

127
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:23,667
A lot.

128
00:06:25,933 --> 00:06:27,500
Leon,

129
00:06:29,433 --> 00:06:32,467
Monette's killer
who hasn't been caught yet,

130
00:06:33,633 --> 00:06:35,833
and Andy, who is still
out there on the loose.

131
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:40,467
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

132
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:43,567
I'm also worried about
our safety at the hotel.

133
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:46,933
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

134
00:06:46,933 --> 00:06:51,900
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

135
00:06:51,900 --> 00:06:53,400
[LUNA SIGHS SOFTLY]

136
00:06:54,133 --> 00:06:56,633
As time goes by,
I can't help but think

137
00:06:56,633 --> 00:06:58,967
something bad
has happened to Leon.

138
00:07:00,133 --> 00:07:07,100
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

139
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:11,400
Luna, I'm always here for you.

140
00:07:12,633 --> 00:07:14,700
I will always be by your side.

141
00:07:14,733 --> 00:07:19,933
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

142
00:07:19,933 --> 00:07:21,633
But I think it would be best

143
00:07:21,633 --> 00:07:23,733
if you stayed away
from the hotel.

144
00:07:25,833 --> 00:07:27,600
But what about you?

145
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:30,167
I thought we were
in this together?

146
00:07:30,167 --> 00:07:32,400
My brothers and I
can handle this.

147
00:07:33,133 --> 00:07:35,967
What I can't handle
is losing you, Luna.

148
00:07:35,967 --> 00:07:41,833
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

149
00:07:41,833 --> 00:07:43,867
It'll be hard for me
not to see you,

150
00:07:43,867 --> 00:07:45,967
but this is the
right thing to do.

151
00:07:45,967 --> 00:07:50,967
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

152
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:53,933
Tell this to your siblings.

153
00:07:53,933 --> 00:07:56,533
Go home and do not return
to Hotel 88.

154
00:07:56,533 --> 00:08:03,467
[MUSIC TURNS MOROSE]

155
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:16,100
[UPBEAT MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

156
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:18,167
[EDWARD]
Boss, another one.

157
00:08:18,167 --> 00:08:21,100
Sir Edward, are you sure
you haven't had enough yet?

158
00:08:22,233 --> 00:08:24,033
Don't worry about me.

159
00:08:24,033 --> 00:08:26,067
I'm fine.

160
00:08:26,067 --> 00:08:27,000
Another one.

161
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:34,000
[UPBEAT MUSIC CONTINUES
IN BACKGROUND]

162
00:08:43,933 --> 00:08:44,967
Alone?

163
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:50,000
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

164
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:53,000
Where could he be?
He's always here.

165
00:08:56,533 --> 00:08:57,767
Yeah.

166
00:08:57,767 --> 00:08:59,200
Alone.

167
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,867
You?

168
00:09:00,867 --> 00:09:03,833
Unfortunately, I'm also alone.

169
00:09:07,933 --> 00:09:09,167
[EDWARD SIGHS SOFTLY]

170
00:09:10,733 --> 00:09:13,833
Well, good thing I'm here.

171
00:09:13,833 --> 00:09:14,967
Tracey.

172
00:09:18,633 --> 00:09:20,033
Edward.

173
00:09:20,033 --> 00:09:22,267
- Nice to meet you.
- Yeah, I know you.

174
00:09:23,900 --> 00:09:26,000
- How?
- Social media.

175
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,633
[EDWARD SCOFFS]

176
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:29,967
- You follow me?
- Nope.

177
00:09:29,967 --> 00:09:32,000
I just see you on my FYP.

178
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:34,733
But I was never interested
in following you.

179
00:09:34,733 --> 00:09:41,233
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

180
00:09:41,233 --> 00:09:42,300
Where could he be?

181
00:09:42,300 --> 00:09:44,833
This is where he hangs out.

182
00:09:44,833 --> 00:09:47,567
Maybe he's at home.
Want to check?

183
00:09:47,567 --> 00:09:49,733
After what happened
between him and Andy,

184
00:09:49,733 --> 00:09:52,067
I doubt he would stay there.

185
00:09:52,067 --> 00:09:53,967
Good point.

186
00:09:53,967 --> 00:09:56,667
I know he has a pod here.

187
00:09:56,667 --> 00:09:58,267
Then let's check there.

188
00:09:58,267 --> 00:09:59,600
Not yet, Kiko.

189
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,000
Let's look here first.

190
00:10:09,633 --> 00:10:11,267
There he is!
There he is!

191
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:20,100
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

192
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:30,667
Uh...

193
00:10:31,700 --> 00:10:32,767
Jade?

194
00:10:32,767 --> 00:10:37,833
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

195
00:10:37,867 --> 00:10:39,267
[BOTTLES CLINK]

196
00:10:44,933 --> 00:10:46,033
Come on.

197
00:10:46,867 --> 00:10:48,833
Let's go home.

198
00:10:48,833 --> 00:10:50,400
- Jade!
- Kiko!

199
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:51,900
Let's go!

200
00:10:51,900 --> 00:10:56,067
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

201
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:58,533
[TRACEY] So...

202
00:10:58,533 --> 00:11:01,133
In other words, you love her?

203
00:11:01,133 --> 00:11:06,133
[CLUB MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

204
00:11:06,133 --> 00:11:07,500
So much.

205
00:11:08,167 --> 00:11:10,767
[TRACEY] Why don't you
just tell her then?

206
00:11:10,767 --> 00:11:12,767
Hiding one's feelings
isn't cute anymore, you know.

207
00:11:12,767 --> 00:11:15,167
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

208
00:11:15,167 --> 00:11:16,733
I'm not hiding my feelings.

209
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:20,533
I just can't look her
in the eye.

210
00:11:20,533 --> 00:11:21,767
[CHUCKLES]

211
00:11:21,767 --> 00:11:22,900
[TRACEY] Why?

212
00:11:28,167 --> 00:11:30,600
Knowing that my father
is the reason why

213
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:32,767
her family is having problems.

214
00:11:32,767 --> 00:11:35,767
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

215
00:11:35,767 --> 00:11:37,733
How can I look at her then?

216
00:11:39,733 --> 00:11:40,900
Wow.

217
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:43,467
Well. That's deep.

218
00:11:46,467 --> 00:11:48,067
[EDWARD] You know what?
I'm sorry.

219
00:11:48,533 --> 00:11:50,700
I'm really letting all
of this out on you.

220
00:11:50,700 --> 00:11:52,867
- Do I seem toxic?
- No, no, no, no.

221
00:11:52,867 --> 00:11:53,900
[TRACEY] It's okay.

222
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:57,100
People say it's better to
open up to strangers

223
00:11:57,100 --> 00:11:58,333
because, you know,

224
00:11:58,333 --> 00:12:00,400
- there's no judgment.
- There's no judgment.

225
00:12:01,533 --> 00:12:05,067
But seriously, I hope
you can fix it together.

226
00:12:05,067 --> 00:12:07,067
She seems like a good catch.

227
00:12:07,067 --> 00:12:09,833
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

228
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:10,833
[GLASSES CLINK]

229
00:12:10,833 --> 00:12:12,133
Cheers.

230
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:16,167
She is.

231
00:12:16,567 --> 00:12:17,533
[KIKO] Jade.

232
00:12:17,533 --> 00:12:18,433
Jade.

233
00:12:18,433 --> 00:12:19,867
What do you want
to hear from me, huh?

234
00:12:19,867 --> 00:12:21,000
Jade!

235
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:24,133
[JADE] Okay, fine!

236
00:12:24,700 --> 00:12:25,700
[INHALES SHARPLY]

237
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:28,100
Yes, I'm hurting.

238
00:12:28,100 --> 00:12:29,867
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

239
00:12:29,867 --> 00:12:33,533
[CRYING]

240
00:12:33,533 --> 00:12:36,000
I'm worried about him.

241
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:38,800
Then all I'll see is
him like that?

242
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:41,000
This whole time,

243
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:41,967
I was thinking about him,

244
00:12:41,967 --> 00:12:44,967
but he already had
someone else in mind.

245
00:12:45,167 --> 00:12:46,767
Is that enough for you?

246
00:12:46,767 --> 00:12:49,167
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

247
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:52,733
It's all right to worry and
think about others even if...

248
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:56,067
Even if you're not the one
they're thinking of.

249
00:12:58,200 --> 00:13:00,767
[KIKO] I understand
how you feel, Jade.

250
00:13:01,533 --> 00:13:04,167
It hurts, but what can you do?
It's just how things are.

251
00:13:04,167 --> 00:13:07,767
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

252
00:13:07,767 --> 00:13:09,167
[INHALES SHARPLY]

253
00:13:09,167 --> 00:13:10,733
I'm sorry, Kiko.

254
00:13:17,167 --> 00:13:18,533
I'm sorry, Kiko.

255
00:13:18,533 --> 00:13:19,667
I know that...

256
00:13:19,867 --> 00:13:22,200
you never really liked Edward,
and yet...

257
00:13:22,867 --> 00:13:24,700
you still accompanied me here.

258
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:29,000
I'm not doing this for him.

259
00:13:30,033 --> 00:13:31,867
I'm doing this for you.

260
00:13:31,867 --> 00:13:35,867
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

261
00:13:35,867 --> 00:13:38,000
[KIKO] Jade, I worry about you.

262
00:13:40,700 --> 00:13:42,167
Not only as a friend.

263
00:13:47,867 --> 00:13:49,833
I've liked you for
a while now, Jade.

264
00:13:51,167 --> 00:13:52,167
[INHALES DEEPLY]

265
00:13:52,167 --> 00:13:53,767
Ever since we were still kids.

266
00:13:53,767 --> 00:14:00,167
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

267
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:02,567
I just couldn't tell you then
because...

268
00:14:02,567 --> 00:14:04,933
I preferred to keep
our friendship.

269
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:09,633
It was more important to me
that you were there.

270
00:14:09,633 --> 00:14:11,767
I would be fine even if
that was the end of it.

271
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:16,767
I was scared that if
I confessed my feelings...

272
00:14:18,333 --> 00:14:20,800
I might lose you in my life.

273
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:23,933
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

274
00:14:23,933 --> 00:14:25,900
Back then,
I told myself that...

275
00:14:27,167 --> 00:14:28,733
it was fine.

276
00:14:29,900 --> 00:14:32,700
That I'd be fine as long
as you were happy.

277
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:34,367
Even if I wasn't
the reason behind it.

278
00:14:34,367 --> 00:14:35,800
[SNIFFS]

279
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:40,200
And then, I saw how happy
you were with Edward.

280
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:46,800
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

281
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:51,100
Jade, he made you smile
in a way that I couldn't.

282
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:56,167
[KIKO] And that's when
I realized...

283
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:59,167
how much it hurt.

284
00:15:02,967 --> 00:15:04,100
[SNIFFLES]

285
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:06,200
That's how much it would hurt...

286
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:08,200
to see you happy.

287
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:15,167
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

288
00:15:19,633 --> 00:15:22,000
- Kiko, I'm sorry.
- Hey! Don't apologize.

289
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:23,333
[KIKO] I'm fine.

290
00:15:23,333 --> 00:15:25,967
Why are you saying sorry?
You've done nothing wrong.

291
00:15:25,967 --> 00:15:27,100
Besides...

292
00:15:27,733 --> 00:15:29,100
That was my choice.

293
00:15:29,967 --> 00:15:31,333
I accepted that.

294
00:15:31,733 --> 00:15:33,000
I have chosen to...

295
00:15:33,700 --> 00:15:35,333
love you silently.

296
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:40,733
Because you are more
important than my feelings.

297
00:15:40,733 --> 00:15:47,700
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

298
00:15:49,967 --> 00:15:52,767
Why are you just
telling me this now?

299
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:57,167
Jade, I'm not saying this
so you'll choose me.

300
00:15:58,300 --> 00:16:01,367
I'm also not saying this
to make Edward look bad.

301
00:16:01,367 --> 00:16:04,200
I just want you to understand
why I worry about you

302
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:06,200
and why I'm not letting go.

303
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:10,200
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

304
00:16:10,233 --> 00:16:12,067
I don't know what to say.

305
00:16:12,067 --> 00:16:13,200
[KIKO] Jade, no.

306
00:16:14,833 --> 00:16:16,800
[KIKO] You don't have
to say anything.

307
00:16:18,233 --> 00:16:22,800
Besides, you don't have to
reciprocate my feelings for you.

308
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:28,233
I just wanted to be honest
with you right now.

309
00:16:28,233 --> 00:16:35,167
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

310
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:37,767
There is...

311
00:16:37,967 --> 00:16:39,767
just one thing I wanted
to ask of you.

312
00:16:42,067 --> 00:16:43,200
What is it?

313
00:16:45,933 --> 00:16:47,033
I hope that...

314
00:16:47,233 --> 00:16:49,033
nothing changes between us.

315
00:16:50,233 --> 00:16:51,767
I hope you don't get
awkward with me

316
00:16:51,767 --> 00:16:54,000
just because I told you
how I feel.

317
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:57,733
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

318
00:16:57,733 --> 00:16:59,700
Nothing will change, Kiko.

319
00:17:01,067 --> 00:17:02,433
I won't be awkward.

320
00:17:03,133 --> 00:17:05,933
Thank you for
being honest with me.

321
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:15,967
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

322
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:18,800
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

323
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:20,767
Hello. How may I help--

324
00:17:20,767 --> 00:17:21,667
[DOOR CLOSES]

325
00:17:22,167 --> 00:17:23,400
[SARI] Why are they here?

326
00:17:24,300 --> 00:17:25,533
It's already late.

327
00:17:25,533 --> 00:17:27,167
- [KNOCKING ON DOOR]
- [CHESKA] Sari.

328
00:17:27,167 --> 00:17:28,767
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

329
00:17:28,767 --> 00:17:29,767
Sari?

330
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:31,500
[DOOR OPENS]

331
00:17:31,500 --> 00:17:33,200
What are you doing here?

332
00:17:34,533 --> 00:17:37,100
Sari, we have
nowhere else to go.

333
00:17:37,700 --> 00:17:40,200
Raphie said we can stay here.

334
00:17:40,767 --> 00:17:42,533
We don't want to go back
to Manila.

335
00:17:42,533 --> 00:17:44,200
Raphie talked you into this?

336
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:45,733
[TRIXIE] Sari, please.

337
00:17:45,733 --> 00:17:47,333
We will help out
with the chores.

338
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:50,667
Sir Martin told you to go home.

339
00:17:50,700 --> 00:17:52,267
Just do what he says.

340
00:17:54,367 --> 00:17:56,300
Sally, you really
won't let us in?

341
00:17:58,567 --> 00:17:59,700
I'm sorry.

342
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:02,300
I don't want to get
in trouble with him.

343
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:04,267
You should go home.

344
00:18:06,700 --> 00:18:08,567
Come on, Cheska. Let's go.

345
00:18:08,567 --> 00:18:09,733
Where are we going?

346
00:18:10,367 --> 00:18:11,533
We'll figure it out.

347
00:18:13,700 --> 00:18:15,100
Sorry for bothering you.

348
00:18:15,767 --> 00:18:17,767
Thank you, Grandpa.

349
00:18:18,567 --> 00:18:20,733
[TRIXIE] Grandpa, thank you.
We're going now.

350
00:18:31,167 --> 00:18:32,533
You should rest up.

351
00:18:34,933 --> 00:18:38,167
Grandpa, you know that my
loyalty lies with Sir Martin.

352
00:18:38,800 --> 00:18:40,600
That's why I said
you should go to sleep.

353
00:18:42,567 --> 00:18:44,333
Where are they going to sleep?

354
00:18:45,167 --> 00:18:48,300
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

355
00:18:48,300 --> 00:18:49,833
Fine, fine.

356
00:18:51,167 --> 00:18:52,767
[SARI] Cheska! Trixie!

357
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:02,533
[TRIXIE] I knew it.
You won't be able to resist us.

358
00:19:03,500 --> 00:19:05,500
You didn't give me a choice.

359
00:19:07,267 --> 00:19:08,433
Thank you, Sari.

360
00:19:08,433 --> 00:19:09,367
Thank you.

361
00:19:09,367 --> 00:19:10,600
- Hmm.
- Grandpa.

362
00:19:11,300 --> 00:19:12,367
Thank you.

363
00:19:12,367 --> 00:19:13,400
- What?
- Thanks.

364
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:14,567
- Thinks?
- I said thanks.

365
00:19:14,567 --> 00:19:15,767
Hmm, yes. Come in.

366
00:19:15,767 --> 00:19:17,433
Thank you, Grandpa.

367
00:19:20,533 --> 00:19:21,933
- Good night, Grandpa.
- Hmm...

368
00:19:21,933 --> 00:19:27,600
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

369
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:29,300
[DOOR CLOSES]

370
00:19:34,333 --> 00:19:38,467
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

371
00:19:38,467 --> 00:19:39,700
What are you doing here?

372
00:19:42,300 --> 00:19:43,533
[SIGHS]

373
00:19:43,533 --> 00:19:44,667
Don't be surprised.

374
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:47,400
I paid for this place.

375
00:19:51,333 --> 00:19:52,833
How could you do that to me?

376
00:19:55,467 --> 00:19:56,467
[SCOFFS]

377
00:19:59,467 --> 00:20:00,800
I already warned you.

378
00:20:02,700 --> 00:20:04,300
You shouldn't be surprised.

379
00:20:07,367 --> 00:20:08,600
You betrayed me.

380
00:20:10,333 --> 00:20:12,467
[EDWARD] You ruined
our lives, Dad.

381
00:20:14,467 --> 00:20:17,267
Your selfishness
has consumed you.

382
00:20:19,767 --> 00:20:20,933
Just for you.

383
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:23,033
All of this is for you.

384
00:20:23,033 --> 00:20:24,967
No. I don't believe that.

385
00:20:26,767 --> 00:20:29,967
I don't want to be involved
in what you do.

386
00:20:30,733 --> 00:20:33,000
You don't understand
how much you've hurt me.

387
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:39,500
Do you think you're
the only one hurting?

388
00:20:41,667 --> 00:20:43,067
You weren't just my father.

389
00:20:43,067 --> 00:20:45,333
You were my best friend, Dad.

390
00:20:47,900 --> 00:20:50,433
But now I don't know
who you really are.

391
00:20:52,667 --> 00:20:56,300
I'm not going to let you
get worse.

392
00:20:56,300 --> 00:20:58,367
We have to find a way
to help you.

393
00:21:01,467 --> 00:21:02,533
Okay.

394
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:06,000
Okay.

395
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:12,533
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

396
00:21:12,567 --> 00:21:13,733
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

397
00:21:20,733 --> 00:21:22,900
This is the last time
you're going to see me.

398
00:21:25,433 --> 00:21:27,767
From now on,
consider me dead.

399
00:21:29,100 --> 00:21:30,533
Okay, fine.

400
00:21:38,967 --> 00:21:40,800
[GIO] I'm really thinking
about all these X marks.

401
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:42,067
I wonder what they are for.

402
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:44,567
We might have to go
to those spots.

403
00:21:45,100 --> 00:21:48,733
But Papa said that the
treasure was in Hotel 88.

404
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:51,367
He probably wouldn't
give us a hard time

405
00:21:51,367 --> 00:21:53,400
trying to find it.

406
00:21:53,667 --> 00:21:55,067
Martin, this is a big property.

407
00:21:55,067 --> 00:21:56,633
What? Do you want us
to blow the place up

408
00:21:56,633 --> 00:21:57,700
just so we can find it?

409
00:21:57,700 --> 00:21:59,000
[MARTIN] Of course not.

410
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:00,833
That's why we're looking
at the clues.

411
00:22:01,367 --> 00:22:02,600
[KIKO] And look at this.

412
00:22:03,367 --> 00:22:04,533
It's the only one.

413
00:22:04,933 --> 00:22:06,900
It doesn't match anywhere.

414
00:22:08,533 --> 00:22:11,633
It's probably there
to confuse us.

415
00:22:11,633 --> 00:22:13,867
Besides, Papa didn't leave that.

416
00:22:13,867 --> 00:22:15,800
So it's possible
that it's not important.

417
00:22:16,567 --> 00:22:18,633
Martin, there's no other way.

418
00:22:20,167 --> 00:22:21,867
It will all just make sense

419
00:22:21,867 --> 00:22:24,000
if we're able to match the maps.

420
00:22:25,900 --> 00:22:28,067
So, we're not going
to the marked spots

421
00:22:28,067 --> 00:22:30,067
until we've completed the maps.

422
00:22:30,067 --> 00:22:32,700
That is why we need
a clue from the book.

423
00:22:35,833 --> 00:22:37,100
Give me the book.

424
00:22:37,100 --> 00:22:38,533
I'll try to find it.

425
00:22:38,533 --> 00:22:39,733
No.

426
00:22:39,733 --> 00:22:41,367
Jade and I can do it, Martin.

427
00:22:42,033 --> 00:22:44,933
We're the ones who started it,
so we have to finish it.

428
00:22:44,933 --> 00:22:46,533
I talked to Luna.

429
00:22:46,733 --> 00:22:49,733
We decided that we shouldn't
bother the Almazans for now.

430
00:22:50,733 --> 00:22:52,200
But, Gio, I think...

431
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:54,700
Jade would want the two of us
to finish it.

432
00:22:55,567 --> 00:22:57,033
I'll talk to her.

433
00:22:57,033 --> 00:22:58,767
If she says no, that's okay.
I can do it by myself.

434
00:22:58,767 --> 00:23:04,000
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

435
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:12,333
- [DARK MUSIC PLAYING]
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

436
00:23:21,267 --> 00:23:24,500
Money really can do wonders
for people like you.

437
00:23:25,467 --> 00:23:26,900
You were released immediately.

438
00:23:28,533 --> 00:23:31,333
[ANDY] They're blaming me
for your crimes.

439
00:23:31,333 --> 00:23:34,400
That's a small price to pay
for what you did to me.

440
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:36,900
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

441
00:23:36,900 --> 00:23:38,900
What happened to you, Sandro?

442
00:23:39,467 --> 00:23:41,633
We had a deal, right?
But you suddenly disappeared.

443
00:23:41,633 --> 00:23:42,933
You killed my son.

444
00:23:42,933 --> 00:23:44,833
[ANDY] It was Marina
who killed Juan.

445
00:23:45,600 --> 00:23:47,300
Yeah, I had Juan abducted.

446
00:23:47,300 --> 00:23:48,867
Because I was looking for you.

447
00:23:49,333 --> 00:23:51,333
But it still happened.

448
00:23:51,333 --> 00:23:52,667
So I'm going to make you pay.

449
00:23:52,667 --> 00:23:54,567
[ANDY] Oh, so what do you
want to happen, huh?

450
00:23:55,300 --> 00:23:57,700
You're going to kill me
and Edward?

451
00:23:57,733 --> 00:23:58,700
[SCOFFS]

452
00:23:58,700 --> 00:23:59,900
You can't do that.

453
00:24:00,500 --> 00:24:03,433
I know why you're still
doing all this.

454
00:24:05,233 --> 00:24:08,933
You've been keeping tabs
on Michael's and Fred's kids...

455
00:24:11,533 --> 00:24:13,967
because you're waiting for them
to complete the maps.

456
00:24:15,733 --> 00:24:18,367
What if I told you
I have one of the maps?

457
00:24:18,867 --> 00:24:19,967
You're lying.

458
00:24:19,967 --> 00:24:26,933
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

459
00:24:29,367 --> 00:24:30,800
[ANDY] You know this is real.

460
00:24:31,633 --> 00:24:32,533
[MAP RIPPING]

461
00:24:32,533 --> 00:24:33,600
No!

462
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:34,800
[GRUNTING]

463
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:36,767
I've got another copy!

464
00:24:39,767 --> 00:24:41,467
I've got another copy.

465
00:24:43,300 --> 00:24:45,000
But you're never getting
your hands on it.

466
00:24:47,267 --> 00:24:48,200
Okay?

467
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:49,967
This is what's going
to happen, Sandro.

468
00:24:51,033 --> 00:24:53,600
Let's go back
to the original plan.

469
00:24:55,633 --> 00:24:57,367
I know you've got one map.

470
00:24:57,900 --> 00:25:00,000
And Michael's kids
have the others.

471
00:25:00,967 --> 00:25:02,767
Once we put
all the pieces together,

472
00:25:02,800 --> 00:25:04,867
nothing will be able to stop us.

473
00:25:06,533 --> 00:25:07,567
Deal?

474
00:25:07,567 --> 00:25:14,533
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

475
00:25:27,300 --> 00:25:29,467
<i>The person who killed Monette
is nearby.</i>

476
00:25:29,467 --> 00:25:30,733
<i> Go home!</i>

477
00:25:30,733 --> 00:25:32,800
<i>Don't give the rest of us
one more thing to worry about.</i>

478
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:35,500
<i>Are you saying
we're a burden?</i>

479
00:25:35,533 --> 00:25:39,333
<i>I'm going to use you
to get what I want!</i>

480
00:25:39,333 --> 00:25:40,600
<i> You're a monster, Sandro!</i>

481
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:44,800
<i>Who was the last person
my son spoke to before he died?</i>

482
00:25:44,800 --> 00:25:45,867
<i> Justin.</i>

483
00:25:46,667 --> 00:25:47,800
<i> No.</i>

484
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:48,900
<i> No!</i>

485
00:25:48,900 --> 00:25:50,400
<i>Even if it killed me,
I wouldn't back down.</i>

486
00:25:50,400 --> 00:25:52,767
<i>Justin, where do you think
we are on the map?</i>

487
00:25:52,967 --> 00:25:55,367
<i>What part of the map
do you think this place is?</i>
